Questions to clarify the scope:

    What does "running data through hashing algorithms until unusable" actually mean as a concrete program behavior? Hashing is one-way — you feed data in, you get a fixed-size digest out, and you can't reverse it. So walk through it: what's the actual input, and what's the actual output of your tool? Is the goal to produce garbage-but-similar-looking data, or to produce a digest/fingerprint of the original data?

